title: Reconcilable Differences
description: Its the first day at Hilmen, and Denise needs to settle with a roommate.

title: Pilot
description: Denise finds out that her dorm payment check bounced and that her checking account is overdrawn.

title: Rudy and the Snow Queen
description: Denise's little sister Rudy visits Hillman and makes Whitley her new role model.

title: Sometimes You Get the Bear, Sometimes the Bear Gets You
If Chosen, I May Not Run
The Prime of Miss Lettie Bostic
I've Got the Muse in Me
Breaking Up Is Hard to Do
For She's Only a Bird in a Gilded Cage
Take This Job and Love It
No Means No
description: Dwayne fears that Freddie may face date rape when she goes out with an aggressive athlete.

title: Strangers on a Plane
description: Dwayne and Whitley get to know one another better on an eventful plane ride back to campus while everyone else adapts to the now co-ed dorms.

title: For Whom the Jingle Bell Tolls
Pride and Prejudice
description: While shopping for her father's birthday present, a jewelry store clerk discriminates against Whitley. Civilians Dwayne and Walter go on a ROTC weekend trip with Col. Taylor and Cadet Sgt. Ron.

title: A World Alike
description: Freddie and transfer student Julian's plans to protest South African apartheid cause Kim to reconsider accepting a need scholarship.

title: That's the Trouble with You All
description: Whitley fixes Dewayne up with another girl, but then has trouble dealing with it.

title: A Camp Fire Story
description: Dwayne and Walter weave a tall tale about their basketball-recruiting trip, which took some strange turns.

title: Hillman Isn't Through with You Yet
description: Whitley has a touch of "senioritis", but it's her job prospects that look a little sickly. Ron's sister, Rachel visits.

title: 21 Candles
description: Whitley is Little Miss Lonely when she thinks everyone's forgotten her 21st birthday.

title: Sweet Charity
description: Whitley, Jaleesa, and Freddie secretly plan to raise money for Kim; and Dwayne and Ron portray hoopsters in a commercial.

title: Soldier Boy
description: Awaiting an ROTC dinner where Col. Taylor is to be roasted, Ron sweats bullets over the choosing of "cadet of the year"

title: Getaway: Part 1
description: While on vacation, Dwayne and Ron gain possession of some drug peddlers' cash and drugs. Part 1 of two.

title: Getaway: Part 2
description: Conclusion. Dwayne and Ron try to thwart the drug dealers by posing as girls.

title: Perhaps Love
description: Dwayne's mom visits when Dwayne is inducted into an honors society. Julian asks Whitley to spend summer with him in DC.

title: How Bittersweet It Is
description: Whitley uses Ron as a pawn in her love match with Dwayne; Freddie tries historics and dramatics to get into a history class.

title: Blues for Nobody's Child
description: Freddie befriends an orphan and suggests the possibility of adopting the boy to Prof. Randolph.

title: Whitley's Last Supper
description: Kim moves into high gear for practice med-school exam, While Whitley downshifts her spending.

title: The Goodwill Games
description: Dwayne helps Whitley prepare for an academic competition, but one thing leads to another during a study session.

title: Tales from the Exam Zone
description: Dwayne, Whitley, and Freddie find themselves in a different dimension--"The Exam Zone".

title: Good Help Is Hard to Fire
description: Dwayne's mother walks in on a squabble between Kinu and the apartment's new maid - Whitley.

title: The Apple Doesn't Fall
description: Col. Taylor feels he's made a hole in one when asked to join the once segregated country club.

title: I'm Dreaming of a Wayne Christmas
description: Whitley joins Dwayne in Brooklyn for his family's Christmas. However she runs into trouble with a crooked Santa while shopping for a gift for Dwayne's mother.

title: War and Peace
description: Blaie Underwood plays a friend of Dwayne's who battles ambivalence on the eve of his reserve unit's departure to Persian Gulf.

title: Ex-Communication
description: Julian has a talk with Whitley that takes a toll on her ego--and may cost her Dwayne.

title: Risk Around the Dollar
description: Lack of money may make Whitley's world come tumbling down after she blows her rent money.

title: Love, Hillman-Style
description: Matthew brings members of the National theater of the Deaf to Walter's outreach center for a performance.

title: Monet Is the Root of All Evil
If I Should Die Before I Wake
Home Is Where the Fire Is
In the Eye of the Storm
The Cat's in the Cradle
description: At a hotly contested Hillman-Virginia A&M game, Ron accepts a sucker bet from three white A&M students, then gets into a fight with them when one of them starts to spray a racial epithet on his car in revenge. In a cell, the men proceed to give very different accounts, mediated by a white officer who challenges both groups' assumptions.

title: Love Taps
description: Events take a tragic turn at the dorm when Lena suspects a rapper named Dion is abusing Gina.

title: Save the Best for Last: Part 1
Save the Best for Last: Part 2
Don't Count Your Chickens Before They're Axed
